name: v0.4.7
body:
## Changelog
* a9ea057 Pick up security fixes with new Go version (#105)

name: v0.4.6
body:
## Changelog

- Fix: `-rpc-timeout` was being ignored since v0.4.3 (#91)
- Feature: Now offering cross-platform container images for linux/amd64, linux/arm64, linux/arm, linux/ppc64le and linux/s390x using [distroless])(https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/distroless) base images.

name: v0.4.4
body:
## Changelog

- Fixes a critical bug rendering the tool unusable in v0.4.3 release (which is now unpublished)
- Feature: add custom gRPC metadata (headers) using the `-rpc-header` option.
- Updated the runtime to go1.16.

name: v0.4.3
body: ⚠️ This release has been unpublished as it contains a [critical bug](https://github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-health-probe/pull/72#issuecomment-876480753) rendering the tool unusable.

name: v0.4.0
body:
- Feature: support for fetching TLS credentials from SPIFFE
- Feature: support for endpoints serving with GZIP
- Feature: now offering OCI/docker images for releases (only linux/amd64 for now) e.g.

      docker pull ghcr.io/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-health-probe:v0.4.0

name: v0.3.3
body:
Some security fixes, although they were not previously exposing an attack vector since this probe is meant to be used against trusted server code you wrote and over the loopback network interface.

- Security: Bump to go 1.15 to build the binary (CVE-2020-14039)
- Security: Bump x/text package (CVE-2020-14040)

name: v0.3.0
body: - Feature: Added -user-agent flag to configure UA string

name: v0.2.0
body:
- Feature: Added a verbosity flag -v
- Feature: Added a --service flag for Check rpc
- Feature: Friendly errors for timeouts
- Fix: Pin to grpc-go =v1.14.0 as the health.proto changed in 1.15.
